// Aïobi OS — aiobi-update audit hooks.
//
// Any apt/apt-get transaction — whether run by aiobi-update itself or
// by a user/admin invoking apt directly — is appended to the same log
// aiobi-update writes to (/var/log/aiobi-update.log, tailed by
// `aiobi-update --log`). This keeps one audit trail for "what changed
// the package set" regardless of which tool triggered it.
//
// The hooks delegate to a shell script rather than inline shell to
// sidestep APT config parser edge cases with nested \" and $() —
// the previous inline form failed with "Extra junk after value".
// The script itself swallows errors so a broken log dir never
// fails the apt transaction it observes.

DPkg::Pre-Invoke  { "/usr/local/lib/aiobi-update/hook.sh pre";  };
DPkg::Post-Invoke { "/usr/local/lib/aiobi-update/hook.sh post"; };
